    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-24T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-24T22:00:00-05:00" n="131"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">548.G1/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hamilton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton, Bermuda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-24T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 24, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 25—2:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>141. For Long from Dodds. The British delegates today agreed to recommend to
                    their Military Authorities that the possibility of using Cyrenaica as a place of
                    refuge for Greek or Polish refugees be reexamined. It was felt that this would
                    be a practical illustration of a mutual desire to include on an equal basis
                    refugees of all races and nationalities. Their attitude suggested confidence
                    approval by their Military. [Dodds.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
